verses_english:
Pass me not, O gentle Savior,
hear my humble cry;
while on others thou art calling,
do not pass me by.

Chorus:
Savior, Savior, hear my humble cry;
while on others thou art calling,
do not pass me by.

verses_yoruba:
Gb‘adura wa, Oba aye
‘Gbat‘ a wole fun O;
Gbogbo wa n kigbe n‘irele,
A n bebee fun aanu;
Tiwa l‘ebi, Tire l‘aanu,
Mase le wa pada;
Sugbon gbo ‘gbe wa n‘ite Re
Ran adura wa lowo.

Chorus:
Wa, wa sodo Mi;
Wa, wa sodo Mi;
Alaare t‘orun n wo;
Wa, wa sodo mi.

Maa wi, ‘tori ranse Re n gbo,
Mo duro de oro Re;
Mo fe gbohun iwosan Re;
Je k‘emi gbo Oluwa,
Mo teti sile Oluwa
S‘ohun t‘O fe wi fun mi.

verses_english:
We are never never weary of the grand old song;
Glory to God, Hallelujah;
We can sing it loud as ever, with our faith more strong
Glory to God, Hallelujah;

Once I fought to conquer sin,
While it reigned my soul within;
Till my Saviour came one day;
Then He triumphed over all,
When He heard my pleading call,
And He took my sins away

Chorus:
Count your blessings, name them one by one;
Count your blessings, see what God hath done;
Count your blessings, name them one by one;
Count your many blessings, see what God hath done.

verses_yoruba:
Mo n kebi at‘oungbe Re Jesu,
Ebi at‘okan wa;
Mo n saferi ‘le mi ni Sion;
N’ ibit‘ Olorun wa.
(Amin).

Itanna didun wa n‘be,
Nile didan yii;
Awon Omode n ko
Orin iyin Jesu;
A! B‘orin naa ti dun to;
Won y‘ite funfun na ka;
Nigbawo ni un o ri O,
Ile didan didan yii?

verses_english:
Chorus:
Believe it, O sinner, believe it;
Receive the glad message -'tis true;
Trust now in the crucified Savior,
Salvation He offers to you.

From death unto life He has brought us,
And made us by grace sons of God;
A fountain is opened for sinners;
Oh, wash and be cleansed in the blood!

Accept now God's offer of mercy;
To Jesus, oh hasten today;
For He will receive him that cometh,
And never will turn him away.
(Amen).

Yield not to temptation, for yielding is sin;
Each victory will help you some other to win;
Fight manfully onward, dark passions subdue,
Look ever to Jesus, He’ll carry you through.

To him that o’ercometh, God giveth a crown;
Through faith we shall conquer, though often cast down;
He who is our Savior our strength will renew;
Look ever to Jesus, He’ll carry you through.
(Amen).

Brightly doth His Spirit shine
Into this poor heart of mine;
While He leads I cannot fall;
Trusting Jesus, that is all.

Singing if my way is clear,
Praying if the path be drear;
If in danger for Him call;
Trusting Jesus, that is all.

Chorus:
Hallelujah! 'tis done; I believe on the Son;
I am saved by the blood of the Crucified One!
Hallelujah! 'tis done; I believe on the Son;
I am saved by the blood of the Crucified One!

Praise Him! praise Him! Jesus, our blessed Redeemer,
For our sins He suffered and bled and died;
He, our Rock, our Hope of eternal salvation,
Hail Him! hail Him! Jesus, the Crucified;
Loving Savior, meekly enduring sorrow,
Crowned with thorns that cruelly pierced His brow;
Once for us rejected, despised, and forsaken,
Prince of Glory, ever triumphant now.

Blessèd Savior, assist us, to rest on Thy Word;
Let the soul healing power, on us now be outpoured;
Wash away every sin-spot, take perfect control,
Say to each trusting spirit, thy faith makes thee whole. (Amen).

Chorus:
We walk by faith, and not by sight;
’Tis God’s own way and must be right;
We walk by faith, and not by sight;
We follow Christ, the Light.

Thro’ Jesus’ death the debt was paid,
Not feeling, nor emotion;
On Him our sin and guilt was laid;
O, give Him your devotion.

Chorus:
Forward! Forward! ’Tis the Lord’s command;
Forward! Forward! To the promised land;
Forward! Forward! Let the chorus ring:
We are sure to win with Christ, our king!

Satan’s fearful onslaughts cannot make us yield;
While we trust in Christ, our buckler and our shield;
Pressing ever on—the Spirit’s sword we wield,
And we follow all the way.

Let our glorious banner ever be unfurled;
From its mighty stronghold evil shall be hurled;
Christ, our mighty captain, overcomes the world,
And we follow all the way.

Praise Him for redemption, Free to every soul;
Praise Him for the Fountain That can make us whole;
For His gifts of kindness, And His loving care,
For the blest assurance, That He answers prayer.

Friends will be there I have loved long ago;
Joy like a river around me will flow;
Yet, just a smile from my Saviour, I know,
Will thro' the ages be glory for me

verses_yoruba:
Oore ti mo fe yoo wa nibe;
Ayo bi odo yoo san yi mi ka;
Mo mo pe un o l‘ayo lodo Jesu
Eyii yoo je ogo fun mi titi.
(Amin).

verses_english:
How sweet the name of Jesus sounds,
Blessed be the name of the Lord;
It soothes his sorrows heals his wounds,
Blessed be the name of the Lord;
Chorus
Blessed be the name, blessed be the name,
Blessed be the name of the Lord;
Blessed be the name, blessed be the name,
Blessed be the name of the Lord;

Dear Shepherd! I hear, and will follow Thy call;
I know the sweet sound of Thy voice;
Restore and defend me, for Thou art my all,
And in Thee I will ever rejoice.
(Amen).

verses_yoruba:
Mo fi gbogbo re fun Jesu,
Mo fi'rele wole fun un;
Mo fi gbadun ayé sile;
Gba mi Jesu si gba mi

verses_english:
Be not dismayed whate'er betide,
God will take care of you;
Beneath his wings of love abide,
God will take care of you;

Chorus:
God will take care of you;
Through ev'ry day, o'er all the way;
He will take care of you,
God will take care of you.

No matter what may be the test,
God will take care of you;
Lean, weary one, upon his breast,
God will take care of you.

Chorus:
God will take care of you;
Through ev'ry day, o'er all the way;
He will take care of you,
God will take care of you.

verses_yoruba:
Eru 'ji ko ba mi, won yoo dekun;
'Danwo ko le pa mi, 'tori mo n'alaafia;
Gbogb'ohun ti mo ko sile, n ko fe mo,
Un o r'ohun t'o ju won lo ni Kenaan'.

Chorus:
Awon t'o fe le duro n'Egypt,
Emi n lo si Kenaan'
Nibi wara at'oyin, yoo te wa lorun;
Ti un o ja ajasegun, ti alaafia yoo je temi;
Okan mi yoo sinmi l'ebute Re.

Wahala ko ni 'pa, ko le duro pe;
Won le yi mi ka, un o sa s'odo Jesu;
Gbogbo aye le daru, ko si mi titi;
Ko si iji ni ebute Kenaan'.

verses_english:
Dark is the world, and cold,
Her cares cannot be told;
Come to thy Savior's fold;
O don't stay away.

Time, here, will soon be past,
Moments are flying fast;
Judgment will come at last;
O don't stay away.

verses_yoruba:
Wa, awa n be o, wa;
Wa, ye gb'oke gb'odo;
Wa mura fun ile,
Mase jafara.

chorus_english:
Just now, your doubtings give o'er
Just now, reject Him no more;
Just now, throw open the door;
Let Jesus come into your heart.

verses_english:
Christ, whose glory fills the skies,
Christ, the true, the only Light,
Sun of Righteousness, arise,
Triumph o'er the shades of night;
Dayspring from on high, be near;
Day-star, in my heart appear.

Dark and cheerless is the morn
Unaccompanied by Thee;
Joyless is the day's return
Till Thy mercy's beams I see;
Till they inward light impart,
Glad my eyes, and warm my heart.

O our only Hope and Guide,
Never leave us nor forsake;
Keep us ever at thy side
Till the eternal morning break;
Moving on to Zion's hill,
Homeward still.

Praise God, from whom all blessings flow;
Praise him, all creatures here below;
Praise him above, ye heavenly host:
Praise Father, Son, and Holy Ghost.
(Amen).

Through the day Thy love has spared us;
Now we lay us down to rest;
Through the silent watches guard us,
Let no foe our peace molest;
Jesus, Thou our Guardian be;
Sweet it is to trust in Thee.
Jesus, Thou our Guardian be;
Sweet it is to trust in Thee.

Pilgrims here on earth, and strangers,
Dwelling in the midst of foes;
Us and ours preserve from dangers;
In Thine arms may we repose.
And, when life's sad day is past,
Rest with Thee in Heav'n at last.
Jesus, Thou our Guardian be;
Sweet it is to trust in Thee.
(Amen)

Swift to its close ebbs out life's little day;
Earth's joys grow dim; its glories pass away;
Change and decay in all around I see;
O Thou who changest not, abide with me.

Hold Thou Thy cross before my closing eyes;
Shine through the gloom and point me to the skies.
Heaven's morning breaks, and earth's vain shadows flee;
In life, in death, O Lord, abide with me.
(Amen).

O Savior Christ, our woes dispel;
for some are sick, and some are sad;
and some have never loved thee well,
and some have lost the love they had;

O Savior Christ, thou too art man;
thou has been troubled, tempted, tried;
thy kind but searching glance can scan
the very wounds that shame would hide.

verses_yoruba:
'Wo imole! Laarin ookun aye,
Maa sin mi lo;
Okunkun su, mo si jinna s'ile,
Maa sin mi lo;
To 'sise mi, ohun eyin ola,
Emi ko bere; sise kan to fun mi,

verses_english:
Sweet Savior, bless us; night is come;
Through night and darkness near us be;
Good angels watch about our home,
And we are one day nearer Thee.

Thou art a port, protected
From storms that round us rise;
A garden, intersected
With streams of paradise;
Thou art a cooling fountain
In life's dry, dreary sand;
From thee, like Pisgah's mountain,
We view our promised land.

Great Shepherd of thy people, hear;
thy presence now display;
as thou hast given a place for prayer,
so give us hearts to pray.

Within these walls let holy peace
and love and concord dwell;
here give the troubled conscience ease;
the wounded spirit heal.

verses_yoruba:
Ojo isinmi Olorun,
Ojo ti o dara julo;
Ti Olorun ti fi fun wa;
K'awa k'o sinmi ninu re.

verses_english:
Jesus, we love to meet
On this Thy holy day;
We worship round Thy seat
On this Thy holy day;
Thou tender, heavenly Friend,
To Thee our prayers ascend;
O'er our young spirits bend
On this Thy holy day.

verses_yoruba:
Mo f'ona 'ta at'ekun re;
Ile t'a se loso,
Ile t'a ko fun Olorun;
Lati fi aanu han.

verses_english:
This is the day the Lord hath made;
He calls the hours His own;
Let Heav'n rejoice, let earth be glad,
And praise surround the throne.

Cold our services have been;
Prayers and praises stained with sin;
But thou canst and wilt forgive;
By thy grace alone we live.

Lord of the harvest, Thee we hail!
Thine ancient promise doth not fail;
The varying seasons haste their round;
With goodness all our years are crowned;
This holy day, Our thanks we pay,
Oh, let our hearts in tune be found.

Flocks that whiten all the plain;
Yellow sheaves of ripened grain;
Clouds that drop their fattening dews,
Suns that temperate warmth diffuse.

verses_yoruba:
Fun ire t' oko n mu wa;
Fun ounje t' a n mu wa;
Fun eso igi pelu;
At' ororo ti a nlo.

Fun gbogb' eran osin wa
T' oun siri oka gbigbo;
Orun ti n se 'ri sile;
Oorun ti n m' oru re wa.

Jesu Oluwa ka wa ye 
Si 'joba ologo yii; 
Ka le dapo m'awon t'orun; 
Lati maa yin O laelae.

verses_english:
All our good is Thine alone;
All our evil is our own;
Oh drive it from before Thy throne,
Come to us; Come.

verses_yoruba:
Oru bu koja tan
Osan ku si dede;
Iboju fere ya
T'o bo Olugbala;
Sanma ti o di wa loju
L'a fere tu kakiri na.

E gb'ori yin soke,
Igbala sunmo 'le,
Wo bi oorun ti iran,
Oju orun mole;
Eniyan mimo, e si maa yo;
Oluwa fere f'ara han.

Fun yin ni Oluwa,
Pese ile didan;
Ko si 'kaanu nibe
Kik' ayo l'o kun 'be;
Eyin mimo, bere si 'yo,
E fere gbohun Angeli na.

Wa, gba oran Baba Re ro;
Si mu ogo Re han;
Wa, ji oku iranse Re
K'o si so won d'otun.

verses_english:
Rejoice, the Lord is King!
Your Lord and King adore;
Rejoice, give thanks, and sing,
And triumph evermore;
Lift up your heart, lift up your voice;
Rejoice, again I say, rejoice!

Jesus, the Savior, reigns,
The God of truth and love;
When He had purged our stains
He took His seat above;
Lift up your heart, lift up your voice;
Rejoice, again I say, rejoice!

His kingdom cannot fail,
He rules o'er earth and Heav'n,
The keys of death and hell
Are to our Jesus giv'n;
Lift up your heart, lift up your voice;
Rejoice, again I say, rejoice!

Rejoice in glorious hope!
Jesus the Judge shall come,
And take His servants up
To their eternal home;
We soon shall hear th' archangel's voice;
The trump of God shall sound, rejoice!

Every Island, sea and mountain
Heaven and earth, shall flee away;
All who hate Him must, confounded,
Hear the trump proclaim the day;
Come to judgement!
Come to judgement! Come away

O may we keep and ponder in our mind
God's wondrous love in saving lost mankind;
Trace we the Babe, who hath retrieved our loss,
From His poor manger to the bitter Cross;
Tread in His steps, assisted by His grace,
Till man's first heavenly state again takes place.

Then may we hope, the angelic hosts among,
To sing, redeemed, a glad triumphal song;
He that was born upon this joyful day
Around us all His glory shall display;
Saved by His love, incessant we shall sing
Eternal praise to heaven's almighty King.

verses_yoruba:
Ji, 'wo Kristian, k'o ko oro ayo
Ti a bi Olugbala araye;
Dide, k'o korin ife Qlorun
T'awon Angeli n ko n'ijo kinni;
Lat' odo won n'ihin naa ti bere;
Ihin Om'Olorun t'a bi s'aye.

Nigbanaa gba ba de orun lohun
A o korin ayo t'irapada;
Ogo eni t'a bi fun wa loni,
Yoo maa ran yi wa ka titi laelae;
A o maa korin ife Re titi,
Oba Angeli, Oba eniyan.

verses_english:
Angels from the realms of glory,
Wing your flight o'er all the earth;
Ye, who sang creation's story,
Now proclaim Messiah's birth;
Come and worship, Come and worship,
Worship Christ, the new-born King.

Shepherds in the field abiding,
Watching o'er your flocks by night;
God with man is now residing,
Yonder shines the infant light;
Come and worship, Come and worship,
Worship Christ, the new-born King.

verses_yoruba:
Ki India on Afrika
K'alaigbede gbogbo ri
Isegun nla t'o logo ni;
T'ori oke Kalfari;
K'ihinrere; k'ihinrere
Tan lat' ilu de ilu.

verses_english:
Joy to the world! The Lord is come;
Let earth receive her King;
Let every heart prepare Him room,
And heaven and nature sing, (2ce)
And heav'n, and heav'n and nature sing.

Joy to the earth! The Saviour reigns;
Let men their songs employ;
While fields and floods, rocks, hills and plains,
Repeat the sounding joy, (2ce)
Repeat, repeat the sounding joy,

True God of true God,
Light from Light Eternal,
Lo, He shuns not the Virgin's womb;
Son of the Father,
Begotten, not created;

Sing, choirs of angels,
Sing in exultation;
O sing, all ye citizens of heaven above!
Glory to God,
All glory in the highest;

Yea, Lord, we greet Thee,
Born this happy morning;
Jesus, to Thee be all glory given;
Word of the Father,
Now in flesh appearing.

My times are in Thy hand;
My God, I wish them there;
My life, my friends, my soul I leave
Entirely to Thy care.

As a shadow, life is fleeting;
As a vapor so it flies;
For the old year now retreating
Pardon grant, and make us wise;

verses_yoruba:
Jesu t'o joko lor' ite,
L'a fi Halleluya wa fun;
Nitori Re nikansoso
L'a da wa si lati korin;
Ran wa lowo lati kaanu
Ese odun t'o ti koja;
Fun ni k'a lo eyii ti n bo,
S' iyin Re, ju odun t'o LO.

verses_english:
In the heavenly country bright,
Need they no created light;
Thou its light, its joy, its crown,
Thou its sun which goes not down;
There forever may we sing
Alleluias to our king!

verses_yoruba:
Kabiyesi! Isun 'bukun
Oba, Baba araiye;
Keferi r'ore- ofe gba
Nwon si nwo agbala Re;
Awa wole, awa dupe,
A n' ipo n'nu Ijo Re;
A nf' igbagbo woo go Re,
A nyin ore- ofe Re.

verses_english:
Reveal Thine strength oh Lord;
Over, above, the earth;
Let all the nations of the world
Look unto God, their King.

verses_yoruba:
Oluwa, f'ipa han;
Lori gbogbo aiye;
Ki gbogbo orile- ede
W' Oba Olorun won.

Enyin enia Olorun,
Okunkun yi aye ka;
So ihin ayo ti Jesu
Ni gbogb' orile- ede;
Ihin ayo, Ihin ayo
Ti 'toye Olugbala.

Gbat' ewu nla ba de si yin;
Jesu yoo dabobo nyin;
Laarin ota at' alejo,
Jesu yoo je Ore nyin;
Itoju Re, Itoju Re
Yoo pelu yin tit' opin.

Gbo! orin ti Jubeli,
O dabi sisan aara;
Tabi bi kikun okun,
Gbat' igbi re ba n lu 'le;
Halleluia! Olorun
Olodumare joba;
Halleluia! k'oro naa
Dun yi gbogbo aye ka.

verses_english:
Rejoice, for Jesus reigns
Enthroned in human hearts;
He breaks the prison chains
And makes them free indeed;
The devil might God's child oppose
No fear of foe, God's word goes on.

The work of righteousness,
Tidings of truth and peace;
For comfort in our life
Shall spread all round about;
Gentiles and Jews shall all bow down
And will worship acceptably.

There's power with Thee for the
Protection of Thine own;
And to Thy high decree
Shall millions take heed to;
The heav'ns rejoice to see Thy work
The islands far hear Thy command.

This perfect heav'nly seed
Shall grow to a big tree;
Like the blessed leaven
Shall spread all o'er the earth;
Till God the Son comes back again
It will go on, Amen, Amen

verses_yoruba:
Irugbin t'orun yii
O fere d'igi nla;
Abukun wukara
Ko le saitan kiri;
Tit' Olorun Omo tun wa
Ko le sailo, Amin! Amin!

verses_english:
What though the spicy breezes
Blow soft o'er Ceylon's isle;
Though ev'ry prospect pleases
And only man is vile;
In vain with lavish kindness
The gifts of God are strown;
The heathen in his blindness
Bows down to wood and stone.

verses_yoruba:
Lat'oke tutu Grinland,
Lati okun India;
Nib'odo oorun Afrik,
N'san yanrin wura won;
Lati' opo odo 'gbaani;
Lati igbe ope,
Won n pe wa k'a gba 'le won,
L'ewon sina won.

verses_english:
Even if I want to be good,
I will stray immediately;
Thy word is always good to me;
But evil, I do always.

verses_yoruba:
Sibe bi mo fe se rere,
Lojukanna mo sina;
Rere l’ oro Re I maa so;
Buburu l’ emi si n se.

verses_english:
Go, labor on while it is day:
The world’s dark night is hastening on;
Speed, speed thy work, cast sloth away;
It is not thus that souls are won.

Press on, and in thy work rejoice;
For work comes rest, the prize thus won;
Soon shalt thou hear the Master’s voice,
The midnight cry, Behold, I come!

verses_yoruba:
Maa sise lo, maa yo pelu
Leyin ise ‘wo o sinmi;
O fere gbohun Jesu na;
Yoo ke tantan pe, Emi de.

verses_english:
Speed Thy servants, Saviour, speed them;
Thou art Lord of winds and waves,
They were bound, but Thou hast freed them;
Now they go to free the slaves;
Be Thou with them: Be Thou with them:
'Tis Thine arm alone that saves.

In the midst of opposition,
Let them trust, O Lord, in Thee;
When success attends their mission,
Let Thy servants humble be;
Never leave them, Never leave them,
Till Thy face in heaven they see:

There to reap in joy forever
Fruit that grows from seed here sown;
There to be with Him, Who never
Ceases to preserve His own;
And with triumph, And with triumph
Sing a Saviour’s grace alone.

verses_yoruba:
Sin awon onse Re, sin won:
’Wo’ Oba efufu, igbi;
Ade won, O da won sile;
Nwon n lo’da eru n’ide:
Wa pelu won, Wa pelu won,
Apa Re l’o le gbala.

Won f’ile at’ore sile,
Bi ase Re Oluwa;
N’ile ati loju omi,
Je Alafehinti won;
Joo pelu won: Joo pelu won:
Si maa to won lailewu.

’Biti ’se won ko m’eso wa,
To dabi ’se won j’asan;
Sunmo won l’aanu Re, Jesu,
Mu ireti won duro;
Ran won lowo, Ran won lowo,
K’ itara won tun soji.

N’nu opolopo isoro,
K’ won gbekele O jesu;
Gbat’ ise naa ba si n gbile,
Ki won mase gberaga;
Ma fi won ’le, Ma fi won ’le,
Titi nwon o r’oju Re.

verses_english:
You alone are the Father’s Son
The only King for ever;
Human beings are great sinners;
Angels are Your messengers.

verses_yoruba:
Iwo nikan l’ Omo Baba
Iwo l’ Oba titi lae;
Eniyan j’ elese pupo;
Angeli ni ’ranse Re.

verses_english:
The prince’s shall worship,
Their offerings they shall bring;
The pow’r of God to praise
Emmanuel our King;

From far distance
They shall worship;
The world would bow
To His command.

verses_yoruba:
Om’ alade y’o sin,
Nwon o mu ore wa;
Lati yin agbara
Immanuel Oba;

Ile jijin
Yio josin;
Aiye y’o gba
Ase Re gbo.

verses_english:
Go, thou mighty Gospel, conquering on thy way;
Night upon the mountains changes into day;
Idols bow before thee, heathen temples fall;
Soon the world shall own thee victor over all.

Tell it out among the nations that the Lord is King;
Tell it out! Tell it out!
Tell it out among the nations, bid them shout and sing;
Tell it out! Tell it out!
Tell it out with adoration that He shall increase,
That the mighty King of glory is the King of Peace;
Tell it out with jubilation, let the song ne'er cease;
Tell it out! Tell it out!

Tell it out among the people, Jesus reigns above;
Tell it out! Tell it out!
Tell it out among the nations that His reign is love;
Tell it out! Tell it out!
Tell it out among the highways and the lanes at home,
Let it ring across the mountains and the ocean's foam,
That the weary, heavy-laden, need no longer roam;
Tell it out! Tell it out!

Blessing abound where'er He reigns;
The prisoner leaps to lose his chains;
The weary finds eternal rest;
And all the sons of want are blest.

verses_yoruba:
Tu Emi Re s‘okan wa,
L‘enu-ona Re l‘a n ke;
K‘ ilekun aanu to se.

verses_english:
He wept, that we might weep;
Each sin demands a tear;
In heaven alone no sin is found,
And there's no weeping there.

Sinful, sighing to be blessed;
bound, and longing to be free;
weary, waiting for my rest:
God be merciful to me.

verses_yoruba:
Irobinuje Okan!
Nko gbodo gboju soke;
Iwo sa mo edun mi;
Qlorun, saanu fun mi.

Jesu, agbara mi,
Iwo l‘aniyan mi;
Emi fi igbagbo woke,
Iwo l‘o n gb’adura;
Je ki n duro de O
Ki n le se ife Re;
Ki iwo Olodumare
K’o so mi di otun.

Fun mi l‘eru orun,
Oju t’o mu hanhan;
T‘yoo wo O n‘gb‘ese sunmole,
K’ori b‘Esu ti n sa;
Fun mi ni emi ni
T‘o ti pese tele;
Emi t’o n duro gangan lae,
T‘o nf’adura sona.

verses_english:
God pities all my griefs;
He pardons every day;
Almighty to protect my soul,
And wise to guide my way.

verses_yoruba:
A f’ayo ro oore-ofe
T‘ Alufa giga wa;
Okan Re kun fun iyonu;
Inu Re n yo fun ‘fe.

verses_english:
Thine eye, Thine ear, they are not dull
Thine arm can never shorten'd be;
Behold me here; my heart is full;
Behold, and spare, and succour me

verses_yoruba:
L‘ooro Iwo o gbohun mi;
L‘afemojumo ojo naa;
Ni odo Re l‘emi o wo,
Si O l‘emi o gb’agbara.

verses_english:
Weary of wandering from my God,
And now made willing to return,
I hear, and bow me to the rod;
For Thee, not without hope, I mourn;
I have an Advocate above,
A Friend before the Throne of Love.

Thou know'st the way to bring me back,
My fallen spirit to restore;
O for Thy truth and mercy's sake
Forgive, and bid me sin no more;
The ruins of my soul repair,
And make my heart a house of prayer.

Lord, I confess to Thee
Sadly my sin;
All am tell I Thee,
All I have been:
Purge Thou my sin away,
Wash Thou my soul this day;
Wash Thou my soul this day;
Lord, make me clean.

Other refuge have I none,
Hangs my helpless soul on Thee;
Leave, ah! leave me not alone!
Still support and comfort me;
All my trust on Thee is stayed,
All my help from Thee I bring;
Cover my defenseless head
With the shadow of Thy wing.

Plenteous grace with Thee is found
Grace to cover all my sin;
Let the healing streams abound,
Make and keep me pure within;
Thou of life the Fountain art,
Freely let me take of Thee;
Spring Thou up within my heart,
Rise to all eternity.

verses_yoruba:
Aabo mi, emi ki o ni,
Iwo l‘okan mi ro mo;
Ma f’emi nikan sile;
Gba, mi si tu mi ninu,
Iwo ni mo gbekele;
Iwo ni’ ranlowo mi;
Ma sai f’iye apa Re
D’aabo b‘ori aibo mi.

verses_english:
Rock of Ages, cleft for me,
let me hide myself in thee;
let the water and the blood,
from thy wounded side which flowed,
be of sin the double cure;
save from wrath and make me pure.

Not the labors of my hands
can fulfill thy law's demands;
could my zeal no respite know,
could my tears forever flow,
all for sin could not atone;
thou must save, and thou alone.

Nothing in my hand I bring,
simply to the cross I cling;
naked, come to thee for dress;
helpless, look to thee for grace;
foul, I to the fountain fly;
wash me, Savior, or I die.

verses_yoruba:
K' ise ise owo mi,
Lo le mu ofin Re se;
B' itara mi ko l'are,
T' omije mi n san titi;
Won ko to fun etutu,
'Wo nikan l'o le gbala.

Ko s'ohun ti mo mu wa,
Mo romo agbelebu;
Mo wa, ko d'aso bo mi,
Mo n wo o fun iranwo;
Mo wa s’ ib'orisun ni,
We mi, Olugbala mi.

Bi mo ti ri - Wo o gba mi,
‘Wo o gba mi, t‘owo t‘ese;
‘Tori mo gba ‘leri Re gbo;
Olugbala, mo de.

Jesu, nigba' danwo,
Gbadura fun mi;
K’emi ma ba se O,
Ki n si sako lo;
‘Gba n ba n siyemeji
K'O bojuwo mi;
K’eru tab' isaju,
Ma mu mi subu.

verses_english:
I lay my wants on JESUS;
All fullness dwells in Him;
He heals all my diseases,
He doth my soul redeem.
I lay my griefs on JESUS,
My burdens and my cares;
He from them all releases,
He all my sorrow shares.

Come, ye sinners, poor and wretched,
Weak and wounded, sick and sore;
Jesus ready stands to save you,
Full of pity joined with power;
He is able, He is willing, doubt no more;

Come, ye needy, come, and welcome;
God’s free bounty glorify:
True belief and true repentance,
Every grace that brings us nigh;
Without money, Come to Jesus Christ and buy;

Come, ye weary, heavy laden,
Bruised and mangled by the fall;
If you tarry till you’re better,
You will never come at all;
Not the righteous, Sinners Jesus came to call;

Lo! th’incarnate God, ascended,
Pleads the merit of His blood;
Venture on Him, venture wholly;
Let no other trust intrude;
None but Jesus, Can do helpless sinners good;

Jesus, I will trust thee, trust without a doubt:
whosoever cometh, thou wilt not cast out;
faithful is thy promise, precious is thy Blood;
these, my soul's salvation, thou my Savior God.

verses_yoruba:
Baba alaanu t‘o fe wa,
Mo gb‘okan mi si O;
Ipa Re t‘o po l‘o gba wa;
Awa n korin si O.

verses_english:
Nothing ye in exchange shall give;
Leave all you have and are behind;
Frankly the gift of God receive;
Pardon and peace in Jesus find.

verses_yoruba:
Gbogbo eni t‘oungbe n gbe, wa!
Olorun n pe gbogb‘ elese;
Ran aanu oun ‘gbala lofe;
Ra oor‘-ofe ihinrere.

verses_english:
Wonderful story of love;
Tell it to me again;
Wonderful story of love;
Wake the immortal strain!
Angels with rapture announce it,
Shepherds with wonder receive it;
Sinner, O won’t you believe it?
Wonderful story of love.

Wonderful story of love;
Though you are far away;
Wonderful story of love
Still He doth call today;
Calling from Calvary’s mountain,
Down from the crystal bright fountain,
E’en from the dawn of creation,
Wonderful story of love.

Wonderful story of love;
Jesus provides a rest;
Wonderful story of love;
For all the pure and blest,
Rest in those mansions above us,
With those who’ve gone on before us,
Singing the rapturous chorus,
Wonderful story of love.

“Lord, Thou hast here Thy ninety and nine;
Are they not enough for Thee?”
But the Shepherd made answer: “This of Mine
Has wandered away from Me;
And although the road be rough and steep,
I go to the desert to find My sheep,

But none of the ransomed ever knew
How deep were the waters crossed;
Nor how dark was the night the Lord passed through
Ere He found His sheep that was lost.
Out in the desert He heard its cry,
Sick and helpless and ready to die;

verses_yoruba:
Okan nin’ awon t’ a ra pada,
Ko mo jijin omi naa;
Ati dudu oru ti Jesu koja,
K’ o to r’ agutan Re he;
L’ aginju rere l’o gbo ’gbe re,
O ti ree tan, o si ti ku tan.

Pada, asako s‘ile re;
Were ni, b‘o ba pe,
Ko si ‘dariji n‘iboji;
Ojo aanu kuru;
Pada, pada.

verses_english:
Lord, I hear of showers of blessing,
thou art scattering full and free;
showers the thirsty land refreshing;
let some drops now fall on me;
even me, even me,
let some drops now fall on me.

Pass me not, O God, my Father,
sinful though my heart may be;
thou mightst leave me, but the rather;
let thy mercy light on me;
even me, even me,
let thy mercy light on me.

Pass me not, O gracious Savior,
let me live and cling to thee;
I am longing for thy favor;
whilst thou'rt calling, O call me;
even me, even me,
whilst thou'rt calling, O call me.

Pass me not, O mighty Spirit!
thou canst make the blind to see;
Witnesser of Jesus' merit,
speak the word of power to me;
even me, even me,
speak the word of power to me.

Love of God, so pure and changeless,
blood of Christ, so rich and free;
grace of God, so strong and boundless
magnify them all in me;
even me, even me,
magnify them all in me.

Pass me not; but pardon bringing,
bind my heart, O Lord, to thee;
whilst the streams of life are springing,
blessing others, O bless me;
even me, even me,
blessing others, O bless me.

verses_yoruba:
Ife Olorun ti ki ye;
Eje Krist' iyebiye;
Ore-ofe alainiwon;
Gbe gbogbo re ga n'nu mi.
An' emi! An’emi
Ro ojo naa sori mi!

W ‘Olori Alufa giga,
B‘o ti gbe ebe wa lo;
L‘ogba, O f’ikedun wole
O f’eru dojubole;
Angeli f’idamu duro
Lati ri Eleda bee;
Awa o ha wa l‘aigb‘ogbe,
T‘a mo pe ‘tori wa ni?

Kiki eje Jesu nikan
L‘o le yi okan pada;
Oun l’o le gba wa n‘nu ebi,
Oun l’o le m‘okan wa ro;
Ofin at‘ikilo ko to,
Won ko si le nikan see;
Ero yii lo le m‘okan ro;
Oluwa ku dipo mi;

Jesu, gbogbo itunu wa,
Lat‘ odo Re l’o ti n wa;
Ife, ‘gbagbo, ‘reti, suuru.'
Gbogbo re l‘eje Re ra;
Lat‘ inu ekun Re l‘a n gba,
A ko da ohun kan ni;
Lofe n‘Iwo n fi won tore
Fun awon t‘o s‘alaini.

verses_english:
O come and mourn with me awhile;
And tarry here the cross beside;
O come, together let us mourn;
Jesus, our Lord, is crucified.

Seven times He spoke, seven words of love;
And all three hours His silence cried
For mercy on the souls of men;
Jesus, our Lord, is crucified.

Come, let us stand beneath the cross;
So may the blood from out His side
Fall gently on us drop by drop;
Jesus, our Lord, is crucified.

O love of God! O sin of man!
In this dread act Your strength is tried;
And victory remains with love;
For Thou our Lord, art crucified!

verses_yoruba:
Ara, e wa ba mi sofo;
E wa sodo Olugbala;
Wa, eje k’ a jumo sofo;
A kan Jesu m’ agbelebu.

Emeje l’ Osoro ife;
Idake wakati meta
L’o fi ntoro anu f’ eeyan;
A kan Jesu m’ agbelebu.

verses_english:
Dark was the night, and cold the ground
On which the Lord was laid;
is sweat like drops of blood ran down;
in agony he prayed.

Go to the garden, sinner, see
those precious drops that flow;
the heavy load he bore for thee;
for thee he lies so low.

Then learn of him the cross to bear;
thy Father's will obey;
and when temptations press thee near,
awake to watch and pray.

Finished all the types and shadows
Of the ceremonial law;
Finished all that God had promised;
Death and hell no more shall awe:
It is finished! It is finished!
Saints, from hence your comfort draw.

Tune your harps anew, ye seraphs,
Join to sing the glorious theme;
All in earth, and all in Heaven,
Join to praise Emmanuel’s name;
Alleluia! Alleluia!
Glory to the bleeding Lamb!

verses_yoruba:
Laipe, yoo ja ide iku
Ogo Re y‘o si tan;
Olugbala, ko si ‘rora;
Tabi ‘fe bi Tire.

verses_english:
In perfect love He dies;
For me He dies, for me;
O all atoning Sacrifice,
I cling by faith to Thee.

You that are passing by,
come to Jesus;
Is it in vain to you, that Jesus Christ died?

Your peacemaker,
he who your ransom paid;
Your sins on the lamb, who carried them away,

He died to make sacrifice,
for your sins;
The Father made the Son to suffer, for you;

14. Thirst for us in mercy still;
All Thy holy work fulfill;
Satisfy Thy loving will:
Hear us, holy Jesus.

verses_yoruba:
9. Ki gbogbo awa Tire,
Je omo ile kanna;
Tori Re ka fe ‘ra wa;
Jesu, sanu fun wa.

14 Ma k‘ongbe fun wa sibe,
Sise mimo l‘ara wa;
Te ife Re na l‘orun;
Jesu, sanu fun wa.

verses_english:
4. O hearts bereaved and sore distressed,
Here is for you a place of rest;
Here leave your grief on Jesus’ breast.

verses_yoruba:
3. Iho t’a wo n’nu okuta
Ni a te Olugbala si;
Olorun, Eleda aiye.

4. Enyin t’ ofo se, t’e ndaro,
Nihin n’ isimi wa fun nyin;
Nihin, k’ ibanuje nyin pin.

verses_english:
4. Still with Thee their Sabbath keep
They who neath the altar sleep;
Resting from their labours past,
Waiting for the trumpet’s blast;
When, the new creation done,
Endless joys shall be begun.

5. Jesu, keep us safe from sin;
With them let us enter in,
Danger past and toil at end;
And to those blest joys ascend
There in flesh our God to see,
And adore eternally.

 Be not fretful, my soul, rest in hope;
Do not fear what tomorrow will bring,
Rest, even death itself is the way;
The King’s servant who was sent to you.

3. Rest, my soul, “It is finished”,
Completed His work of salvation;
Rest, everything has been accomplished;
Once and for all, salvation is yours.

verses_yoruba:
 Sinmi okan mi, ni ireti;
Ma beru bi ola ti le ri,
Sa sinmi, iku paapaa l’ ona;
Iranse Oba t’a ran si o.

verses_english:
3. Christ hath the ransom paid;
The glorious work is done;
Oh Him our help is laid;
By Him our victory won.

3. Thou, of life the Author, death didst undergo,
Tread the path of darkness, saving strength to show;
Come, then True and Faithful, now fulfill Thy Word;
’Tis Thine own third morning; rise, O buried Lord!

4. Loose the souls long prisoned, bound with Satan’s chain;
All that now is fallen raise to life again;
Show Thy face in brightness, bid the nations see;
Bring again our daylight: day returns with Thee!

verses_yoruba:
3. ‘Wo Oluwa iye, O wa to ‘ku wo;
Lati f’ipa Re han, O sun n‘iboji;
Wa, Eni Olooto, Si m‘oro Re se,
Ojo keta Re de, jinde Oluwa!

verses_english:
 Alleluia! Alleluia!! Alleluia!!!
The strife is o’er, the battle done;
The victory of life is won;
The song of triumph has begun: Alleluia!

2. The powers of death have done their worst;
But Christ their legions hath dispersed;
Let shouts of holy joy outburst: Alleluia!

3. The three sad days are quickly sped;
He rises glorious from the dead;
All glory to our risen Head! Alleluia!

4. He closed the yawning gates of hell;
The bars from heaven’s high portals fell;
Let hymns of praise His triumphs tell! Alleluia!

verses_yoruba:
2. Gbogbo ipa n‘iku ti lo,
Sugbon Kristi f’ogun re ka;
Aye! e ho iho ayo; — Aleiuya!

3. Ojo meta naa ti koja;
O jinde kuro nin‘oku;
E f’ogo fun Oluwa wa —Aleluya!

5. Halleluya, Halleluya,
Ogo ni fun Olorun;
Halleluya f’Olugbala
Enit‘o segun iku;
Halleluya, f‘Emi Mimo
Orisun ‘fe ‘wa mimo;
Halleluya, Halleluya
F‘Olorun Metalokan.

3. O f’oju aanu at‘ife
Wo awon ti O ra pada;
Awon ni ayo Re;
O ri ayo at‘ise won,
O bebe ki won le segun,
Ki won baa joba lae.

3. F‘eru sin Oluwa,
Si bowo f’ase Re;
F‘ayo wa sodo Re,
F‘iwariri duro;
E kunle fun;
K‘e teriba;
Sot‘ipa Re,
Ki Omo na!

2. O f'ite Re l‘oke
At‘ogo Re sile;
O f' ife sokale,
O sokun, O si ku;
Iya to je tani le wi
Lati gb‘okan wa lowo 'ku?

3. Lati ‘boji; O nde
N‘ isegun lor‘ iku;
O k‘awon ota Re,
T’ o segun lat‘ibe;
O si l‘awon orun koja
N‘ isegun s‘ite Olorun.

5. Jesu, a ko le san
Gbese ‘fe Re t’ a je,
Ko wa ba ti le san;
Gba ‘yin at‘ope wa,
T‘okan t‘ara wa l’ a fun O;
B’o tile kere, te ‘wo gba.

4. Ojo adura ni;
K‘aye sunmo Orun;
Gb‘okan wa soke sodo Re,
Si pade wa nihin.

5. Oba Ojo l‘eyii;
Fun wa ni isoji;
Ji oku okan wa s‘ife;
Wo asegun iku.

verses_english:
2. Hosanna Lord! thine angels cry;
Hosanna Lord! thy saints reply;
Above, beneath us, and around,
Both death and living swell the sound:

verses_yoruba:
2. Hosanna l’orin Angeli,
Hosanna l’orin ti a n gbe;
L’oke, nisale, yi wa ka,
Oku at’ aaye n gbe ’rin naa;

4. Baba, je ki njere be;
Samona mi laye yi;
F‘oore-ofe pa mi mo;
Fun mi laye lodo Re;
Iwo l‘orun, at‘asa;
To okan isina mi,
Iwo l‘orisun ore,
Ro ojo Re s‘ori mi.

2. Ayo b’awon ti n sin,
Nibiti’ Olorun yan;
Ti won n para ibe,
Lati maa josin won;
Won n yin O sa;
Ayo b’awon
T’o fe ona
Oke Sion.

verses_english:
3. He lives, my kind, wise, constant friend;
Who still will keep me to the end;
He lives to raise me from the grave,
And me eternally to save.

verses_yoruba:
4. O n be, lati pese aye,
Yoo si mu mi de ’be layo;
O n be, ogo f’ oruko Re;
Jesu, okanna titi lae.

5. O n be, mo bo low’ aniyan;
O n be, mo bo lowo ewu;
A! ayo l’ oro yii fun mi
“Mo mo p’ Oludande mi n be.”

verses_english:
5. He has raised our human nature
On the clouds to God's right hand;
There we sit in heav'nly places,
There with Him in glory stand.
Jesus reigns, adored by angels;
Man with God is on the throne;
By our mighty Lord's ascension
We by faith behold our own.

verses_yoruba:
5. Iwo ti gbe ara wa WO
Lo s‘ow‘Otun Olorun;
A si joko nibi giga
Pelu Re ninu ogo;
Awon angeli mbo Jesu
Eniyan joko lor‘ite;
Oluwa, b‘Iwo ti goke
Joo je ka le goke be.

3. Baba fi gba agbara
Fun, Jesu Oluwa;
Ogun Angel‘ mbo O;
Oun l‘Oba nla orun.

5. Ota Re l‘ota wa;
Esu, aye,ese;
Sugbon yoo r’eyin won,
Ijoba Re yoo de.

2. Ojo etutu de,
Israeli, e pe;
A ti ru ebo tan,
Ebo Od’agutan;

4. Kristian, e ho f’ayo,
Olorun gb‘ ebo wa;
Jesu n bebe pupo,
Bi Alagbawi wa;

verses_english:
 Thou art gone up on high,
To mansions in the skies;
And round Thy throne unceasingly
The songs of praise arise;
But we are lingering here,
With sin and care oppressed;
Lord, send Thy promised Comforter,
And lead us to Thy rest.

2. Thou art gone up on high;
But Thou didst first come down,
Through earth’s most bitter misery,
To pass unto Thy crown;
And girt with griefs and fears
Our onward course must be;
But only let this path of tears
Lead us at last to Thee.

 He is gone—a cloud of light
Has received Him from our sight;
High in Heav’n, where eye of men
Follows not, nor angels’ ken;
Through the veils of time and space,
Passed into the holiest place;
All the toil, the sorrow done,
All the battle fought and won.

5. He is gone—but we once more
Shall behold Him as before;
In the heaven of heavens the same,
As on earth He went and came;
In the many mansions there,
Place for us He will prepare;
In that world unseen, unknown,
He and we shall yet be one.

verses_yoruba:
5. O ti lo lekan sii
A o tun foju wa ri;
O wa bakan naa l’orun
Gege b‘o ti wa l‘aye;
N‘nu ‘bugbe t’o wa nibe
Y’o pese aye fun wa;
Ninu aye ti n bo wa
A o j‘okan pelu Re,

3. Ayo won ti po to;
Awon to ri Jesu,
Nibit‘o gbe gunwa,
T‘a si n fi ogo fun un,
Won n korin iyin Re;
Ati t‘isegun Re;
Won ko dekun royin
Ohun nla t‘o ti se.

verses_english:
6. The LAMB's Apostles there
I might with joy behold;
The harpers I might hear
Harping on harps of gold;

verses_yoruba:
3. Oju gbogbo won n dan,
N’ ile ayo;
N’ ipamo Baba wa,
Ife ki ’ku;
N je sure lo s’ ogo,
Gba ade at’ ijoba;
T’ o mo ju orun lo,
Joba titi.

 Oke kan n be t’ o n dan t’o ga,
Nibi t’ a m’ Olorun;
O wa l’ okere ni orun;
Ite Olorun ni.

verses_english:
3. O Paradise, O Paradise,
'Tis weary waiting here;
I long to be where Jesus is,
To feel, to see Him near;

verses_yoruba:
5. Paradise! Paradise!
Nko ni duro pe mo;
Nisiyi b’enipe mo ngbo
Ohun orin orun;

6. Jesu, Oba Paradise,
Pa mi mo n’nu ’fe Re;
Mu mi de ile ayo na,
Nib’ isimi l’oke;

verses_english:
2. There is no grief in heaven;
For life is one glad day;
And tears are of those former things
Which all have passed away.

1. Brief life is here our portion;
Brief sorrow, short lived care;
The life that knows no ending,
The tearless life, is there.

3. With jasper glow thy bulwarks,
Thy streets with emeralds blaze;
The sardis and the topaz
Unite in thee their rays;
Thine ageless walls are bonded
With amethyst unpriced;
The saints build up thy fabric,
The cornerstone is Christ.

verses_yoruba:
3. Okuta jasper didan,
L’a fi mo odi re;
Oniruru okuta
L’a fi te ita re;
Ilu na dara pupo,
O mo bi kristali;
Awon mimo ni ngbe ’be,
Kristi n’ Ipile re.

verses_english:
7. Come Lord, come Wisdom, Love and Power,
open our ears to hear;
let us not miss the accepted hour;
save, Lord, by love or fear.

verses_yoruba:
7. Wa, ogbon, Ife at‘ Ipa;
Fun ki eti wa si;
K’a ma so akoko wa nu;
Ki ‘fe Re le gba wa.

verses_english:
 Creator Spirit, by whose aid
The world's foundations first were laid,
Come, visit every humble mind;
Come, pour Thy joys on humankind;
From sin and sorrow set us free
And make Thy temples worthy Thee.

3. Plentous of grace, descend from high
Rich in Thy sevenfold energy;
Make us eternal truths receive
And practice all that we believe;
Give us Thyself that we may see
The Father and the Son by Thee.

4. Immortal honor, endless fame,
Attend the almighty Father's name;
The Savior Son be glorified,
Who for lost man's redemption died;
And equal adoration be,
Eternal Paraclete, to Thee.

verses_yoruba:
3. Da opo oore-ofe Re
Lat‘ orun sori gbogbo wa;
Je k’a gba otito Re gbo,
K’a si maa sa ro l‘okan wa;
F‘ara Re han wa k’a le ri
Baba at‘Omo ninu Re.

4. K’a fi ola ati iyin
Fun Baba, Olodumare,
K’a yin ooko Jesu logo;
Enit‘O ku, lati gba wa;
Iyin bakannaa ni fun O
Parakliti ayeraye.

verses_english:
2. To every one whom God shall call
The promise is securely made;
To you far off - he calls you all;
Believe the word which Christ hath said:

verses_yoruba:
2. B‘iro iji lile
Wa kunnu ile yii;
Mi Emi isokan si wa:
Okan kan, imo kan;
Fun ewe at‘agba
L‘ogbon at‘oke wa;
Fi okan gbigbona fun wa
K’a yin, k’a gbadura.

verses_english:
2. Father of the poor, draw near;
Giver of all gifts, be here;
Come, the soul’s true radiancy.

6. Where Thou art not, man hath naught;
Every holy deed and thought
Comes from Thy divinity.

7. What is soilèd, make Thou pure;
What is wounded, work its cure;
What is parchèd, fructify;

8. What is rigid, gently bend;
What is frozen, warmly tend;
Strengthen what goes erringly.

verses_yoruba:
 Wa, Parakliti mimo,
Lat‘ ibugbe Re orun;
Ran itansan ‘mole wa

 Wa mi si wa, Emi Mimo,
Tan’na orun si okan wa;
Emi a f’ororo yanni,
Ti ’f’ebun meje Re funni.
Ise nla Re atoke wa
N’itunu, iye, ina ife;

verses_english:
 Spirit divine, attend our prayer,
And make our heart Thy home;
Descend with all Thy gracious power;
Come, Holy Spirit, come.

6. Spirit divine, attend our prayer;
Make a lost world Thy home;
Descend with all thy gracious powers,
O come, great Spirit, come.

 Light of lights! when falls the even,
let it sink on sin forgiven;
fold us in the peace of heaven;
shed a vesper calm.

verses_yoruba:
 Iyin ainipekun,
Ni ka fun Baba;
Iyin ainipekun,
Ni ki a fun Omo;
Iyin ainipekun
Ni ka fun Emi;
Iyin ainipekun
Fun Metalokan.

 ’Wo Olorun Omo,
T’ O ku lati gba wa;
Enit’ O ji dide,
Ti O si goke lo;
Iwo l’ ogo, ati iyin,
Ope, ati ola ye fun.

verses_english:
 Mine to chide me when I rove,
Mine to show a Savior's love;
Mine thou art to guide and guard;
Mine to punish or reward.

 Loud may the troubled ocean roar;
In sacred peace our souls abide;
While every nation, every shore,
Trembles, and dreads the swelling tide.

 The secrets of the God of heaven;
Ambassador from heaven;
The sword that killed the sting of death,
God’s own iimage divine.

verses_yoruba:
 Asiri Olodumare;
Iko Oba orun;
Ida t‘o pa oro iku,
Aworan Olorun.

 Ibi kan wa ti Jesu n da
Ororo ayo s’ ori wa;
O dun ju ibi gbogbo lo;
Ite- aanu t’ a f’eje won.

verses_english:
 Go, when the morning shineth
Go, when the noon is bright;
Go, when the eve declineth;
Go, in the hush of night;
Go with pure mind and feeling
Fling earthly cares away,
And in thy chamber kneeling
Do thou in secret pray.

 That eye is fixed on seraph throngs;
That arm upholds the sky;
That ear is filled with angel songs;
That love is throned on high.

 Blessed One, whose name is love,
Pleads with Thee Thy Son above;
Broods o’er Thy hovering Dove;
Holy Father, hear us.

 There before Thy mercy-seat
Saints in light and angels meet;
Yet behold us at Thy feet;
Holy Father, hear us.

Grant us in this holy hour
From His bride’s exhaustless dower;
Light and life and peace and power;
Holy Father, hear us.

verses_yoruba:
 Iwo Isun imole;
Ogo ti ko l’ okunkun;
Ayeraiye, titi lae,
Baba Mimo, gbo ti wa.

 Olubukun, Olufe,
Omo Re n be O loke;
Emi Re n rado bo wa;
Baba Mimo, gbo ti wa.

 Okan ti n wa isinmi;
Okan t’ eru ese n pa;
B’ om’- owo ti n ke f’ omu,
Baba Mimo, gbo ti wa.

 F’okan tutu, t’ope fun mi;
Gba mi lowo kikun;
Fun mi n’ ibukun oor’ ofe;
Si je ki n wa fun O.

verses_english:
 Thou spread'st a table in my sight;
Thy unction grace bestoweth;
And O what transport of delight
From Thy pure chalice floweth!

verses_yoruba:
 Iwo te tabili fun mi;
‘Wo d‘ororo s’ori mi;
A! ayo naa ha ti po to
Ti n t‘ odo Re wa ba mi?

Ire ti mo ni, lat’ odo Re ni;
B’ ibi ba de, o je b’o ti fe ni;
B’ Oun j’ore mi, mo la bi n ko ri je,
L’ aisi Re, mo tosi bi mo l’ oro:
Ayida le de; ere tab’ ofo;
O dun mo mi, bi ’n’ ba sa je Tire.

B’ ayida de, mo mo- Oun ki yida;
Oorun ogo ti ki ku, ti ki wo;
O n rin l’ or’ awosanma at’ iji,
O n tanmole s’ okunkun eniyan Re:
Gbogbo n kan le lo, ko ba mi n’nu je,
Bi ’mi’ ba je Tire, ti Oun je temi.

A! laye, n ko mo idaji ’fe Re;
Laabo ni mo n ri, laabo ni mo n sin;
’Gba mo ba f’ oju kan an loke lohun,
Un o feran Re po, un o si yin in jojo:
Un o wi laarin egbe- orin orun,
Bi mo ti je Tire, t’Oun je temi.

verses_english:
In some way or other the Lord will provide.
It may not be my way, it may not be thy way;
And yet, in His own way, “the Lord will provide.”

At some time or other, the Lord will provide:
It may not be my time, it may not be thy time;
And yet in His own time, “the Lord will provide.”

March on then right boldly: the sea shall divide;
The pathway made glorious, with shouting victorious,
We’ll join in the chorus, “The Lord will provide.”

'Tis I, who washed thy spirit white;
'Tis I, who gave thy blind eyes sight;
'Tis I, thy Lord, thy life, thy light:
'Tis I; be not afraid.

This bitter cup, I drank it first;
To thee it is no draught accurst;
The hand that gives it thee is pierced:
'Tis I; be not afraid.

verses_yoruba:
Jesu, Olugbala, wo mi,
Aare mu mi, ara n ni mi;
Mo de lati gb’ ara le O;
’Wo ’sinmi mi.

Bojuwo mi, o re mi tan;
Irin ajo naa gun fun mi;
Mo n wa ’ranwo agbara Re,
’Wo Ipa mi.

verses_english:
Give to the winds thy fears;
Hope, and be undismayed.
God hears thy sighs and counts thy tears;
God shall lift up thy head.

We expect a bright tomorrow;
all will be well;
faith can sing through days of sorrow,
all will be well;
on our Father's love relying,
Jesus every need supplying
in our living, in our dying,
all will be well.

verses_yoruba:
Nipa ife Olugbala,
Ki yoo si nkan;
Ojurere Re ki pada,
Ki yoo si nkan.
Owon l’ eje t’o wo wa san;
Pipe l’edidi oor’ofe;
Agbara l’owo t’o gba ni;
Ko le si nkan.

Bi a wa ninu iponju,
Ki yoo si nkan:
Igbala kikun ni tiwa,
Ki yoo si nkan;
Igbekele Olorun dun;
Gbigbe inu Kristi l’ ere;
Emi si n so wa di mimo;
Ko le si nkan.

verses_english:
Changeless, the way of peace:
changeless, Emmanuel's name;
changeless, the covenant of grace;
eternally the same.
“I change not,” is a Father's word.
“And I am with thee,” saith the Lord.

verses_yoruba:
Nihin l‘ayida wa;
Ojo, erun, n koja,
Ile ni nyan ti o si n sa,
‘Tanna daadaa si n ku;
Sugbon oro Kristi duro:
Un o wa pelu re” ni Oun wi.

Nihin l‘ayida wa;
Sugbon l‘aarin eyii,
L‘aarin ayida yi d‘aye,
Okan wa ti ki yi;
Oro Jehofa kii pada:
Un o wa pelu re”, ni Oun wi.

Ona alaafia;
Immanueli wa;
Majemu ti oore-ofe,
Lae, won ki yipada
N kii yipada,” l‘oro Baba,
Mo o wa pelu re”, ni Oun wi.

verses_english:
We did not mark the chosen few,
When Thou didst through the clouds ascend,
First lift to Heaven their wondering view,
Then to the earth all prostrate bend;
But we believe that mortal eyes
Beheld that journey to the skies;

And now that Thou dost reign on high,
And thence Thy waiting people bless,
No ray of glory from the sky
Doth shine upon our wilderness;
But we believe Thy faithful Word,
And trust in our redeeming Lord;

verses_yoruba:
Om‘Olorun, a ko ri O,
‘Gba t‘O wa s‘aye, iku yii;
Awa ko ri ibugbe Re;
Ni Nasareti ti a gan,
Sugbon a gbagbo p‘ese Re
Ti te ita Re kakiri.

verses_english:
My hope is built on nothing less
Than Jesus' blood and righteousness;
I dare not trust the sweetest frame,
But wholly lean on Jesus' name.
On Christ, the solid Rock, I stand;
All other ground is sinking sand.

When darkness veils His lovely face,
I rest on His unchanging grace;
In every high and stormy gale
My anchor holds within the veil.
On Christ, the solid Rock, I stand;
All other ground is sinking sand.

His oath, His covenant, and blood
Support me in the whelming flood;
When every earthly prop gives way,
He then is all my Hope and Stay.
On Christ, the solid Rock, I stand;
All other ground is sinking sand.

A faith that shines more bright and clear
When tempests rage without;
That when in danger knows no fear;
In darkness feels no doubt.

I thank thee, uncreated Sun,
That thy bright beams on me have shined;
I thank thee, who hast overthrown
My foes, and healed my wounded mind;
I thank thee, whose enlivening voice
Bids my freed heart in thee rejoice.

Uphold me in the doubtful race,
Nor suffer me again to stray;
Strengthen my feet with steady pace
Still to press forward in thy way;
That all my powers, with all their might,
In thy sole glory may unite.

Thee will I love, my Joy, my Crown,
Thee will I love, my Lord, my God;
Thee will I love, beneath thy frown,
Or smile, thy scepter, or thy rod;
What though my flesh and heart decay?
Thee shall I love in endless day!

verses_yoruba:
‘Wo Orun mi, gba ope mi,
Fun ‘mole Re t’o fi fun mi;
Gba ope mi, ‘wo l’o gba mi,
Lowo awon ti n sota mi;
Gba ope mi, fun ohun Re
T’o mu mi yo lopolopo.

Tit’ igbanna ni ohun mi,
Yoo ma rohin ‘fe Re;
Nigba iku, k’ Oruko Re;
F’ itura f’ okan mi.

K‘a dabi Re ninu ife;
L‘ewa iwa mimo;
B‘a ti n woju Re, k‘a maa lo
L‘at‘ ogo de ogo.

verses_english:
Because, O Lord, Thou lovedst us with everlasting love,
And sentest forth Thy son to die that we might live above;
Because, when we were heirs of wrath, Thou gavest hopes of heaven;
We love because we much have sinn'd, and much have been forgiven.

verses_yoruba:
N‘nu ife lo s‘eda aye,
O da eniyan sinu re;
Lati maa s‘akoso gbogbo;
E korin ‘fe Eleda wa.

O ri wa ninu okunkun,
Pe, a ko mo ojubo Re;
N‘ife O fi ona han wa;
E korin ife Oloore!

N‘ife O fi Jesu fun wa,
Omobibi Re kansoso;
O wa ra wa lowo ese;
A yin ‘fe Re Olugbala!

verses_english:
Hark, my soul! it is the Lord;
'Tis thy Saviour, hear His word;
Jesus speaks, and speaks to thee:
Say, poor sinner, lov'st thou Me?

Thou shalt see My glory soon,
When the work of grace is done;
Partner of My throne shalt be;
Say, poor sinner, lov'st thou Me?

Stronger His love than death or hell;
Its reaches are unsearchable;
The first born sons of light

Desire in vain its depths to see;
They cannot reach the mystery
The length, and breadth, and height.

God only knows the love of God;
O that it now were shed abroad
In this poor stony heart!

For love I sigh, for love I pine;
This only portion, Lord, be mine,
Be mine this better part.

Forever would I take my seat
Like Mary at the Master's feet;
Be this my happy choice;

verses_yoruba:
Okan mi n poungbe lati mo
Riri ife irapada;
Ife Krsiti si mi.

Ife Re n’ ipa ju iku;
Oro Re awamaridi!
Awon Angel paapaa

Wa ijinle ife yi ti;
Won ko le mo iyanu naa,
Giga at’ ibu re.

Olorun nikan l’o le mo,
Iba je tan ka ’le loni;
L’ okan okuta yii!

Ife nikan ni mo n toro,
Ko je ipin mi Oluwa;
K’ ebun yii je temi.

Emi iba le joko lae,
Bi Maria, lese Jesu;
K’ eyi je ayo mi:

verses_english:
Jesus, my Lord, my God, my All,
Hear me, blest Savior, when I call;
Hear me, and from Thy dwelling place
Pour down the riches of Thy grace;
Jesus, my Lord, I Thee adore;
O make me love Thee more and more.

Jesus, too late I Thee have sought;
How can I love Thee as I ought?
And how extol Thy matchless fame,
The glorious beauty of Thy name?
Jesus, my Lord, I Thee adore;
O make me love Thee more and more.

Jesus, of Thee shall be my song;
To Thee my heart and soul belong;
All that I have or am is Thine;
And Thou, blest Savior, Thou art mine;
Jesus, my Lord, I Thee adore;
O make me love Thee more and more.

Then shall my latest breath
Whisper Thy praise;
This be the parting cry
My heart shall raise;
This still its prayer shall be:
More love, O Christ to Thee;
More love to Thee, More love to Thee!

verses_yoruba:
Ki nfe o sii Kristi,
Ki nfe o si!
Gb’adura ti mo n gba;
L’ ori ekun mi;
Eyi ni ebe mi;
Ki nfe o sii Kristi
Ki nfe o sii, Ki nfe o sii.

Lekan ohun aye,
Ni mo ntoro
Nisisiyii, ‘wo nikan;
Ni mo n wa;
Eyi l’ adura mi;
Ki nfe o si Kristi
Ki nfe o si, Ki nfe o si.

verses_english:
Jesus, Lord, we look to Thee;
Let us in Thy name agree;
Show Thyself the Prince of peace,
Bid our jars forever cease.

By Thy reconciling love
Every stumbling block remove;
Each to each unite, endear;
Come, and spread Thy banner here.

Free from anger, and from pride;
Let us thus in God abide;
All the depth of love express,
All the height of holiness.

verses_yoruba:
Nipa ilaja Tire
Mu idugbolu kuro;
Da wa po ni isokan;
F‘itegun Re saarin wa.

K‘a s‘aniyan ara wa;
K‘a maa reru ara wa;
K‘a f‘apere fun Ijo,
B‘onigbagbo ti gbe po.

B‘a ti n rin sile, je k‘a
Ran ‘ra wa lowo lona;
O to ka wa nibi gbogbo;
S‘ona gbogbo l‘a dekun,
Ise wa ni, Ise wa ni,
K‘a maa ran ‘ra wa l‘eru.

K‘a gb‘omonikeji wa ga,
Ju b‘a ba ti gbe‘ra wa;
K'a fi keeta gbogbo sile,
K‘okan wa si kun fun ‘fe;
Yio ro wa, Yio ro wa,
B‘a wa n‘ireo l‘aye.

verses_english:
Hands, and hearts, and voices raise;
Sing as in the ancient days;
Antedate the joys above,
Celebrate the feast of love.

Witnesses that Christ hath died,
We with him are crucified;
Christ hath burst the bands of death,
We his quickening Spirit breathe;

Christ is now gone up on high,
Thither all our wishes fly;
Sits at God's right hand above;
There with him we reign in love!

verses_yoruba:
K‘a gb‘okan at‘ohun wa
Soke bi t‘aye ‘gbaani;
K‘a beere ayo orun;
K‘a s‘ajo ase-ife.

Krist‘to goke lo s‘orun,
Oun ni ife wa n fa si;
O wa l‘otun Olorun;
Nibe l‘a o ba joba.

verses_english:
We all partake the joy of one;
The common peace we feel;
A peace to sensual minds unknown,
Is the name of Jesus.

Amazing grace! how sweet the sound!
That saved a wretch like me;
I once was lost, but now am found;
Was blind, but now I see.

Take, my soul, thy full salvation;
Rise o’er sin, and fear, and care;
Joy to find in every station
Something still to do or bear:
Think what Spirit dwells within thee;
What a Father’s smile is thine;
What a Savior died to win thee,
Child of heaven, shouldst thou repine?

There let the way appear,
Steps unto heaven;
All that thou sendest me,
In mercy given;
Angels to beckon me
Nearer, my God, to thee;
Nearer to thee!

Gird thy heavenly armour on;
Wear it ever, night and day;
Ambushed lies the evil one,
Watch and pray.

verses_yoruba:
Wo ‘hamora orun re,
Wo losan ati loru;
Esu ba, o n dode re;
Maa sora.

Gbo b‘Oluwa re ti wi,
Eniti iwo feran;
F‘oro Re si okan re;
Maa sora

verses_english:
I am a stranger here,
Heaven is my home;
Earth is a desert drear,
Heaven is my home;
Danger and sorrow stand
Round me on every hand;
Heaven is my Fatherland
Heaven is my Home.

What though the tempest rage,
Heaven is my Home;
Short is my pilgrimage,
Heaven is my Home;
And time's wild wintry blast
Soon will be overpassed;
I shall reach Home at last;
Heaven is my Home.

Guide me, O thou great Jehovah,
pilgrim though this barren land;
I am weak, but thou art mighty;
hold me with thy powerful hand;
Bread of heaven, Bread of heaven,
feed me till I want no more,

Open now the crystal fountain,
whence the healing stream doth flow;
let the fire and cloudy pillar
lead me all my journey through;
strong Deliverer, strong Deliverer.
be thou still my Strength and Shield,

When I tread the verge of Jordan,
bid my anxious fears subside;
bear me through the swelling current,
land me safe on Canaan's side;
songs of praises, songs of praises,
I will ever give to thee,

Lead us, heavenly Father, lead us
through this world's tempestuous sea;
guard us, guide us, keep us, feed us
for your help is full and free,
here possessing every blessing
if our God our Father be.

Jesus still lead on
Till our rest be won;
And although the way be cheerless,
We will follow calm and fearless;
Guide us by your hand
To our fatherland.

Let your drooping hearts be glad;
March in heavenly armour clad:
Fight, nor think the battle long;
Soon shall victory tune your song.

Lord, be our light when worldly darkness veils us;
Lord, be our shield when earthly armor fails us;
And in the day when hell itself assails us,
Grant us Your peace, Lord.

verses_yoruba:
’Wo le se ranwo, b’ iranlowo aye ye,
’Wo le gba ni la b’oku ese gbija;
Iku at’ Esu ko le bor’ Ijo Re;
F’ alaafia fun wa.

verses_english:
I know not what may soon betide
Or how my wants shall be supplied;
But Jesus knows and will provide.

Against me earth and hell combine;
But on my side is power divine;
Jesus is all and he is mine.

verses_yoruba:
B’o ti wu k’ ija gbona to!
K’a mase gbo pe emi n sa;
’Tori Jesu l’ apata mi.

N ko mo ’hun t’o le de, n ko mo
Bi n ki yoo ti se wa l’aini;
Jesu l’o mo, yoo si pese.

Bi mo kun f’ ese at’ osi,
Mo le sunmo Ite- aanu;
’Tori Jesu l’ ododo mi.

B’ adura mi ko ni laari,
Sibe ’reti mi ki o ye;
’Tori Jesu n bebe loke.

Aye at’ esu n de si mi;
Sugbon Olorun wa fun mi;
Jesu l’ohun gbogbo fun mi.

Olus’ agutan yoo pese,
Yoo fi papa tutu bo mi;
Owo re yoo mu ’ranwo wa,
Oju re yoo si maa so mi;
Yoo maa ba mi kiri losan,
Loru yoo maa dabobo mi.

verses_english:
At the sign of triumph Satan’s host doth flee;
On then, Christian soldiers, on to victory!
Hell’s foundations quiver at the shout of praise;
Brothers, lift your voices, loud your anthems raise.

Led by that, we brave the ocean;
Led by that, the storms defy;
Calm amidst tumultuous motion,
Knowing that our Lord is nigh:
Waves obey Him,
And the storms before Him fly.

O what pleasures there await us:
There the tempests cease to rear;
There it is that those who hate us
Can molest our peace no more;
Trouble ceases
On that tranquil happy shore.

verses_yoruba:
B’a ko mo ’biti a n lo gun si,
Ju b’a ti n gbohun re lo;
Sugb’a ko ’hun gbogbo sile,
A tele ihin t’a gbo;
Pelu Jesu,
A nla aarin ibu lo.

A ko beru igbi okun;
A ko si ka iji si;
Laarin ’rukerudo, a mo
P’ Oluwa n be nitosi;
Okun gba gbo,
Iji sa niwaju Re.

verses_english:
Best of the weary, joy of the sad;
Hope of the dreary, light of the glad;
Home of the stranger, strength to the end;
Refuge from danger, Saviour and Friend.

Pillow, where, lying, love rests its head;
Peace of the dying, life of the dead.
Path of the lowly, prize at the end;
Breath of the holy, Saviour and friend.

verses_yoruba:
Onife nla, Alafeyinti,
Alaafia l’ akoko iku;
Ona at’ ere onirele;
’Wo li emi awon eniyan Re.

verses_english:
All our days direct us in the way we go;
Lead us on victorious over every foe;
Bid Thine angels shield us when the storm-clouds lower;
Pardon Thou and save us in the last dread hour.

verses_yoruba:
Wo asia Jesu ti n fe;
Gbo ohun ipe;
A o segun gbogbo ota
Li oruko Re.

verses_english:
We’ve no abiding city here;
We seek a city out of sight.
Zion its name; the Lord is there;
It shines with everlasting light.

verses_yoruba:
A ko ni ’bugbe kan nihin;
Eyii ba elese n’nu je;
Ko ye k’ eeyan mimo kaanu,
Tori won n fe sinmi t’ orun.

A ko ni ’bugbe kan nihin,
A n wa ilu nla t’ a ko ri;
Sion its name; the Lord is there;
O n tan imole titi lae.

verses_english:
The Son of God goes forth to war,
A kingly crown to gain;
His blood-red banner streams afar;
Who follows in His train?

verses_yoruba:
Egbe mimo; awon wonni;
T‘Emi Mimo ba le,
Awon akoni mejila;
Ti ko ka iku si.

verses_english:
If Thou should’st call me to resign
What most I prize, it ne’er was mine;
I only yield Thee what was Thine;
Thy will be done.

Take my will, and make it Thine;
It shall be no longer mine.
Take my heart, it is Thine own;
It shall be Thy royal throne.

verses_yoruba:
Gba ’fe mi, fi se Tire;
Ki o tun je temi mo;
Gb’ okan mi, Tire n’ ise
Maa gunwa nibe titi.

verses_english:
Has He called thee to the plough?
Onward go! Onward go!
Night is coming serve Him now;
Onward go!
Faith and love in service blend;
On His mighty arm depend;
Standing fast until the end,
Onward go!

In this little moment then,
Onward go! Onward go!
In thy ways acknowledge Him;
Onward go!
Let His mind be found in thee;
Let His will thy pleasure be;
Thus in life and liberty,
Onward go!

Work, for the night is coming, work through the morning hours;
Work while the dew is sparkling, work ’mid springing flowers;
Work when the day grows brighter, work in the glowing sun;
Work, for the night is coming, when man’s work is done.

Work, for the night is coming, work through the sunny noon;
Fill brightest hours with labor, rest comes sure and soon.
Give every flying minute, something to keep in store;
Work, for the night is coming, when man works no more.

Work, for the night is coming, under the sunset skies;
While their bright tints are glowing, work, for daylight flies.
Work till the last beam fadeth, fadeth to shine no more;
Work, while the night is darkening, when man’s work is o’er.

To the work! To the work! Let the hungry be fed;
To the fountain of life let the weary be led;
In the cross and its banner our glory shall be,
While we herald the tidings, "Salvation is free!"

To the work! To the work! There is labor for all;
For the kingdom of darkness and error shall fall;
And the love of our Father exalted shall be,
In the loud-swelling chorus, "Salvation is free!"

Though they are slighting Him, still He is waiting,
Waiting the penitent child to receive;
Plead with them earnestly, plead with them gently;
He will forgive if they only believe.

Rescue the perishing, Duty demands it,
Strength for thy labour the Lord will provide;
Back to the narrow way Patiently win them;
Tell the poor wand’rer a Saviour has died.

verses_yoruba:
Yo awon ti n segbe, - ise tire ni;
Oluwa yio f’agbara fun O;
Fi suuru ro won pada s’ona tooro;
So f’ asako p’ Olugbala ti ku.

verses_english:
Yet when bowed down beneath the load
By heaven allowed, thine earthly lot;
Look up! thou'lt reach that blest abode;
Wait, meekly wait, and murmur not!

Thy life was given for me;
thy blood, O Lord, was shed,
that I might ransomed be,
and quickened from the dead.
Thy life was given for me;
what have I given for thee?

verses_yoruba:
Gb‘agbelebu re n‘ipa Re,
Rora ma la ewu ja lo;
Y‘o mu o de ile ayo;
Y‘o mu o segun iboji.

Ba ni so Oluwa,
Ohun to ye k’a so;
Gegebi oro Re;
Ni ki eko wa
K‘awon agutan Re
Le maa mo ohun Re;
Ibit‘O n to won si
Ki won si le maa yo.

verses_english:
Come, labor on!
The toil is pleasant, the reward is sure;
Blessèd are those who to the end endure;
How full their joy, how deep their rest shall be,
O Lord, with Thee!

Yet there is room: the Lamb’s bright hall of song,
With its fair glory, beckons thee along;
Room, room, still room! O enter, enter now.

Day is declining, and the sun is low;
The shadows lengthen, light makes haste to go;
Room, room, still room! O enter, enter now.

The bridal hall is filling for the feast;
Pass in, pass in, and be the Bridegroom’s guest;
Room, room, still room! O enter, enter now.

Enter in; that banquet is for thee;
That cup of everlasting joy is free;
Room, room, still room! O enter, enter now.

All Heaven is there, all joy! Go in, go in;
The angels beckon thee the prize to win:
Room, room, still room! O enter, enter now.

Louder and sweeter sounds the loving call;
Come, lingerer, come; enter that festal hall;
Room, room, still room! O enter, enter now.

It fills, it fills, that hall of jubilee!
Make haste, make haste; ’tis not too full for thee;
Room, room, still room! O enter, enter now.

Ere night that gate may close, and seal thy doom;
Then the last low, long cry, No room, no room!
No room, no room! O woeful cry, No room!

verses_yoruba:
Ojo n sure, o n koja;
Iku n sure, o de tan;
Elese n sawada ni!
Ojo at‘ iku n wo o

Emi n sure, t‘o ba pin.
‘Wo ko le pada mo lae;
'Wo o bo s‘ainipekun;
Ko ha ye k‘ iwo ronu?'

Mura giri, iku n bo,
B‘o ba duro, o segbe;
Ma sun mo, dide, sare;
"Olugbala n reti re.

verses_english:
Again he comes! from place to place
His holy footsteps we can trace;
He pauses at our threshold, nay,
He enters, condescends to stay;
Shall we not gladly raise the cry?
"Jesus of Nazareth passeth by."

Ho! all ye heavy-laden, come;
Here's pardon, comfort, rest, and home;
Ye wanderers from a father's face,
Return, accept his proffered grace!
Ye tempted, there's a refuge nigh,
"Jesus of Nazareth passeth by."

verses_yoruba:
Sugbon b‘iwo ko ipe yii,
Ti o si gan ife nla Re;
Oun yio peyinda si o,
Yio si ko adura re;
‘O pe ju n‘igbe naa yoo je (2ce)
Jesu ti Nasaret‘ ti koja (2ce)

Nigbat‘ idanwo yi mi ka,
Ti idamu aye mu mi;
T‘ota farahan bi ore
Lati wa iparun fun mi;

Nigbati ko s‘alabaro;
Ti Olutunu si jinna;
T‘ibanuje, b‘iji lile
Te ori mi ba n‘ironu.

Oun kan l‘a ba maa du;
T‘a ba maa lepa re;
Pe k‘igba ‘bewo wa maa lo,
Laitun pada wa mo.

verses_english:
The Spirit calls today:
Yield to His power;
O grieve Him not away;
’Tis mercy’s hour.
(Amen).

You children of the dead,
Who remain in sin still;
Hear you the Gospel call,
Jesus has sent to you;
You miserable rejects come now;
In Jesus’ arms there’s always room.

Do not delay too long,
Eschew all excuses;
He calls you to come now,
Though you are miserable,
You sinner, all things are ready;
There’s room in His arms for all souls.

verses_yoruba:
Enyin omo oku,
T’ o wa ninu ese;
Gbohun ihinrere,
Jesu ranse si yin.
Eyin eni- egbe, e wa;
Ni apa Jesu aaye n be.

E ma pe titi mo,
Ma wa awawi mo;
O ni k’ e wa loni,
Bi e tile ’tosi;
Gbogbo nkan se tan, elese:
Fun gbogbo okan, aaye n be.

Gba oro t’ orun gbo,
Ti onise Re n so;
Alaanu l’ Oluwa,
Ooto l’ oruko Re;
Okan isubu, pada wa,
S’ aigbekele nu, aye n be.

Eyin wo ni tempili Re,
Oluwa t’ a ti n reti;
Woli ’gbani ti so tele;
Olorun m’ oro Re se;
Awon ti a ti ra pada,
Yio fi ohun kan yin in.

verses_english:
These are they who have contended
for their Savior's honor long,
wrestling on 'til life was ended,
foll'wing not the sinful throng;
these, who well the fight sustained,
triumph thro' the Lamb have gained.

verses_yoruba:
Wonyii l’okan won ti gbogbe
Ninu ‘danwo kikoro
Wonyi li o ti f‘adura
Mu Olorun gbo tiwon;
Nisisiyi won segun;
Olorun re won l‘ekun.

verses_english:
Thou wast their Rock, their Fortress, and their Might;
Thou, Lord, their Captain in the well-fought fight;
Thou, in the darkness drear, their one true Light.
Alleluia! Alleluia!

But, lo, there breaks a yet more glorious day;
The saints triumphant rise in bright array;
The King of Glory passes on His way.
Alleluia! Alleluia!

verses_yoruba:
Baba, niwaju ite Re; 
L‘angeli n teriba; 
Nigba gbogbo niwaju Re 
Ni won korin iyin; 
Ni won si n fi ade wura won 
Lele yite naa ka; 
Won n fi ohun pelu duuru 
Korin si Oluwa.

verses_english:
Thy truth unchanged hath ever stood;
Thou savest those that on Thee call;
To them that seek Thee Thou art good,
To them that find Thee all in all.

Draw us to Thy wounded side,
Whence there flowed the healing tide;
Lamb of God, grant us Thy peace.

From the bonds of sin release,
Cold and wavering faith increase;
Lamb of God, grant us Thy peace.

verses_yoruba:
Jesu, ‘Wo oninure
Sin wa lo tabili Re;
Si f’ ounje orun bo wa.

B‘a ti kunle yi O ka,
Je k‘a mo p‘O sunmo wa;
Si f’ ife nla Re han wa.

verses_english:
Here, O my Lord, I see Thee face to face;
Here would I touch and handle things unseen;
Here grasp with firmer hand eternal grace,
And all my weariness upon Thee lean.

I have no help but Thine; nor do I need
Another arm save Thine to lean upon;
It is enough, my Lord, enough indeed;
My strength is in Thy might, Thy might alone.

Mine is the sin, but Thine the righteousness;
Mine is the guilt, but Thine the cleansing blood;
Here is my robe, my refuge, and my peace;
Thy Blood, Thy righteousness, O Lord my God.

verses_yoruba:
Gbat‘ a ba dide t‘a si palemo 
T‘a ko akara ati wain‘ kuro; 
Sibe Iwo wa nihin, Oluwa; 
Lati je Orun ati Asa mi.

verses_english:
Till He come Oh, let the words
Linger on the trembling chords;
Let the little while between
In their golden light be seen;
Let us think how Heaven and home
Lie beyond that ?Till He come.`

verses_yoruba:
K‘Oun to de, ‘je k‘oro yii, 
Maa dun titi l‘eti re; 
Je ki saa die t‘o ku 
Han gbangba daju fun O; 
Ronu b‘orun oun ile 
‘Ti d‘eyin gbat‘O ba de.

verses_english:
Jesus, we lift our souls to Thee;
Thy Holy Spirit breathe;
And let these little infants be
Baptized into Thy death.

Our great captain and our saviour
These children we give to thee;
Pray, make them fit for thy service;
Heirs of life these children are.

Jesus, we lift our souls to Thee;
Thy Holy Spirit breathe;
And let these little infants be
Baptized into Thy death.

Come, Holy Spirit, come;
Oh hear my lowly prayer;
Stoop down, and make my heart Thy home,
And shed Thy blessing there.

Thou didst live to God alone;
Thou didst never seek Thine own;
Thou Thyself didst never please:
God was all Thy happiness.

verses_yoruba:
Mo fe lati wa ‘do Re; 
Oluwa mi, mase ko; 
Oluwa fun mi n’ipo, 
Ninu ‘joba ore Re

Jesu fe mi, mo mo bee; 
Bibeli l’o so fun mi; 
Tire l’ awon omode, 
Won ko lagbara, Oun ni.

verses_english:
For he is our childhood's pattern; 
Day by day, like us He grew;
He was little, weak and helpless,
Tears and smiles like us He knew;
And He feeleth for our sadness,
And He shareth in our gladness.

verses_yoruba:
Ore kan mbe fun omode 
Loke orun lohun; 
Ore ti ki yipada, 
T’ ife Re ko le ku; 
Ko dabi ore aiye 
Ti n baje lodoodun; 
Oruko Re bi ore 
Wo fun nigbagbogbo.

Ile kan n be fun omode 
Loke orun lohun; 
Nibiti Jesu njoba, 
Ile alaafia! 
Ko s’ ile t’ o joo laiye 
T’ a le fi sakawe; 
Ara ro ‘lukuluku; 
Irora naa dopin.

Ade kan n be fun omode 
Loke orun lohun; 
Enit’ o ba n wo Jesu 
Yoo ri ade naa de; 
Ade t’ o logo julo, 
Ti yoo fi fun gbogbo 
Awon ore re laye; 
Awon t’ o fe nihin.

verses_english:
The sun shines its light;
The darkness has fled;
Various joyful sounds are spreading about.

Morning’s my delight,
All Thanks be to God;
He who watches over me when I sleep.

verses_yoruba:
Orun tan mole;
Oru ti sa lo;
Gbogbo ’ro ayo l’o n dun kakiri.

Mo le f‘ori pamo 
S'abe itoju Re; 
Mo mo p‘Olorun n be, 
Lodo mi n ‘gbagbogbo; 
O ye k‘eru ese ‘ba mi (2x) 
Tor‘ Olorun sunmo tosi.

’Wo ko mu pe titi mo
L’ aye ekun oun osi yii;
Iwo si f’ ayo gba a
Si ile orun mimo ni;
O woso ala mimo,
O n ba O gbe n’ imole.

Ju wonni lo, o wi fun won; 
Ohun wonni t‘Olorun fe; 
O si se enit‘o tutu; 
Yio si gbo t‘awon ewe.

Didun l’ oro, at’ iwo Re;
Gb’ awon iya sunmo;
O gbe omo won s’ apa Re,
O si sure fun wom.

verses_english:
Save us, Lord, from sinning;
Watch us day by day;
Help us now to love Thee;
Take our sins away.

verses_yoruba:
Gba wa lowo ese; 
So wa lojojo; 
Je k‘ a le feran Re 
Ko ese wa lo.

‘Gbat‘ O ba si pe wa 
S‘ile wa orun; 
Layo l‘ao dahun pe; 
Oluwa, a de! 
(Amin).

verses_english:
Be present at our table, Lord;
Be here and everywhere adored;
Thy creatures bless, and grant that we
May feast in paradise with Thee. 
(Amen).

verses_yoruba:
Omode yoo wa nibe,
T’ o wa Olorun l’ aye;
Ni gbogbo ’le eko;
A! bi o ti dun to! &c.

’Wo Imole,
Se ’toju mi;
Tan imole Re yi mi ka.

verses_english:
Our many sins forgive;
the Holy Spirit send;
and teach us to begin to live
the life that knows no end.

Lord, fill our hearts with love;
our teacher's labors own;
that we and they may meet above,
to sing before thy throne.
(Amen).

verses_yoruba:
Jesu, jo bukun ile wa; 
K‘a lo ojo yii re; 
K‘a le ri aye lodo Re, 
Jesu ore ewe. 
(Amin).

A o pa de leti odo,
T’ese angeli ti te;
T’o mo gara bi Kristali;
Leba ite olorun?

verses_english:
O let me feel thee near me!
The world is ever near;
I see the sights that dazzle,
The tempting sounds I hear;
My foes are ever near me,
Around me and within;
But Jesus, draw thou nearer,
And shield my soul from sin.

verses_yoruba:
Baba, Eleda gbogbo,
Ninu ogbon Re nla;
Lo so awon meji po
Ninu ogba Eden;
Fifun awon ‘mo Re yi;
Ife atorun wa,
K‘ibukun wa n‘ile won,
Ile t‘Olorun ngbe.

B‘lwo ko ko ile na,
Wuhala asan ni;
B‘IWO ko si n‘ile won,
Asan ni ayo won;
Sugbon ile T‘IWO wa
Idapo didun ni;
‘Biti ife Re ba wa;
Ife ailopin ni.
Amin.

Sinmi le Oluwa - E gbo 
Orin duuru orun; 
Sinmi le‘fe Re ailopin; 
Si duro je.

verses_english:
Thou art my hiding-place, O Lord,
In Thee I put my trust;
Encouraged by Thy holy Word,
A feeble child of dust;
I have no argument beside,
I urge no other plea;
And 'tis enough my Saviour died,
My Saviour died for me.

We would see Jesus; other lights are paling,
Which for long years we have rejoiced to see;
The blessings of our pilgrimage are failing;
We would not mourn them, for we go to Thee.

We would see Jesus: this is all we’re needing;
Strength, joy, and willingness come with the sight;
We would see Jesus, dying, risen, pleading;
Then welcome day, and farewell mortal night. (Amen).

verses_yoruba:
So ’tan naa fun mi pele,
Ki o ba le ye mi;
T’ irapada iyanu,
T’ etutu fun ese;
So fun mi nigbagbogbo,
’Tori n ko pe gbagbe;
Oye ori mi ti lo,
Bi iri owuro.
So itan kanna fun mi, &c.

N ko gbodo yan ‘pin mi; 
N ko tile je yan an; 
Yan fun mi Olorun: 
Beeni un o rin deede.

verses_english:
Thou the shame, the grief, hast known;
Though the sins were not Thine own,
Thou hast deigned their load to bear;
Jesus, Son of Mary, hear!

Thou hast pass’d through death’s dark shade;
Thou hast full atonement made;
Thou to God’s right hand art near,
Son of God, Emmanuel, hear.
(Amen).

verses_yoruba:
’Wo ti gbe ara wa wo;
O si mo banuje wa;
O ti sokun bi awa,
Olugbala, gbo ti wa.

’Wo ti teriba fun ’ku;
’Wo ti t’eje Re sile;
A te O si posi ri;
Olugbala, gbo ti wa.

verses_english:
Ha! they suffer no more cold,
In heaven, In heaven;
Their cold season ever passed,
All their days are bright and fair;
In heaven, In heaven.

verses_yoruba:
A! otutu ki mu won,
Loke orun; Loke orun;
Owo re won ti koja,
Gbogbo ojo l’ o dara;
Loke orun; Loke orun.

verses_english:
Now the laborer’s task is o’er;
Now the battle day is past;
Now upon the farther shore
Lands the voyager at last.
Father, in Thy gracious keeping
Leave we now Thy servant sleeping.

There the tears of earth are dried;
There its hidden things are clear;
There the work of life is tried
By a juster Judge than here.
Father, in Thy gracious keeping

verses_yoruba:
Lala alagbẹe tan;
Ọjọ ogun ti pari;
L’ ebute jijìn réré
Ni ọkọ rẹ ti gùn si:
Baba, labẹ itọju Rẹ,
L’ awa f’ iranṣẹ Rẹ yi si.

Nibẹ l’a rẹwẹn l’ọkún;
Nibẹ, nwọn mọ ohun gbogbo;
Nibẹ l’ Onidaj’ otọ
N dan iṣẹ aiye wọ nibe.
Baba, labẹ itọju Rẹ,

“Ranse Olorun, seun;
Sinmi n’nu laalaa re;
Iwo ti ja, o si segun;
Bo s’ ayo Baba re.”
Ohun naa de loru,
O dide lati gbo;
Ofa iku si wo l’ ara,
O subu, ko beru.

verses_english:
O God of saints! to Thee we cry;
O Savior! plead for us on high;
O Holy Ghost! our Guide and Friend,
Grant us Thy grace till life shall end;
That with all the saints our rest may be
In that bright paradise with Thee! (Amen).

The flow' rs that beautified the field,
That looked tender and fresh;
When touched by sickle, it will die;
It falls and withers off.

The grass, when dead, will wake no more;
Die, thou, that thou may live;
What, if death were door that leads
To everlasting pain.

verses_yoruba:
Koriko, b’o kú, ki ji mọ;
Ẹ kù lati tun yè;
A! b’ iku lẹ jẹ ‘lẹkun nkọ
S’ irora ailopin!

verses_english:
Thou art gone to the grave, but we will not deplore thee;
Though sorrows and darkness encompass the tomb;
The Savior has passed through its portals before thee,
And the lamp of his love is thy guide through the gloom.

The toilsome way thou’st /travell’d /o’er,
And hast borne the heavy load;
But Christ hath taught thy wandering feet
To reach his bless’d abode;

Sin can never taint thee now,
Nor can doubt thy faith assail;
Nor thy meek trust in Jesus Christ
And the Holy Spirit fail;

“Earth to earth,” and “dust to dust,”
Thus the solemn priest hath said;
So we lay the turf above thee now,
And seal thy narrow bed;

The Lord, ye know, is God indeed;
Without our aid He did us make;
We are His folk, He doth us feed,
And for His sheep He doth us take.

O enter then His gates with praise;
Approach with joy His courts unto;
Praise, laud, and bless His name always,
For it is seemly so to do.

For why? The Lord our God is good;
His mercy is for ever sure;
His truth at all times firmly stood,
And shall from age to age endure.

verses_yoruba:
Oluwa, Oun ni Qlorun,
Laisi ’ranwo wa, O da wa;
Agbo Re ni wa, O n bo wa;
O si fi wa s’aguntan Re.

verses_english:
The Church's one foundation
Is Jesus Christ her Lord;
She is His new creation
By water and the word;
From heaven He came and sought her
To be His holy bride;
With His own blood He bought her,
And for her life He died.

Then is my strength by Thee renewed;
Then are my sins by Thee forgiven;
Then dost Thou cheer my solitude
With hopes of heaven.

No words can tell what blest relief,
There for my every want I find;
What strength for warfare, balm for grief;
What peace of mind.

Hushed is each doubt, gone every fear;
My spirit seems in heaven to stay;
And e'en the penitential tear
Is wiped away.
